      • parseRawPacket

        public static HTTPRawPacket parseRawPacket(byte[] httpPacket)
        Parses HTTP packet in form of byte array into a raw (unprocessed) HTTP packet. This means that it splits headers and the rest of the packet without doing any kind of processing.
        Parameters:
        httpPacket - is a whole HTTP packet in byte array form
        Returns:
        HTTPRawPacket object

      • parsePacket

        public static HTTPPacket parsePacket(byte[] httpPacket)
        Parses HTTP packet in form of byte array into HTTPPacket object. Same as parsePacket(HTTPRawPacket) and parseRawPacket(byte[]) combined.
        Parameters:
        httpPacket - is a whole HTTP packet in byte array form
        Returns:
        HTTPPacket object

      • parsePacket

        public static HTTPPacket parsePacket(HTTPRawPacket rawHttpPacket)

        Returns:
        HTTPPacket object

      • parseCookie

        public static HTTPCookie parseCookie(java.lang.String rawCookie)

        Parameters:
        rawCookie - is the string representation of cookie
        Returns:
        HTTPCookie object

      • getHeaderStream

        public static java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream getHeaderStream(byte[] rawHttpPacket)
        Gets a byte array stream containing the header of a HTTP packet + '\r\n' at the end. Calling .size() gives you the body offset, which is the same as the length of header + '\r\n'.
        Parameters:
        rawHttpPacket - is the raw http packet as byte array
        Returns:
        ByteArrayOutputStream containing bytes of header

      • getBodyStream

        public static java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream getBodyStream(byte[] rawHttpPacket,
                                                          int bodyOffset)
        Gets a byte array stream containing the body of a HTTP packet. This is often used in conjunction with getHeaderStream(byte[])
        Parameters:
        rawHttpPacket - is the raw http packet as byte array
        bodyOffset - is the offset into rawHttpPacket that marks the start of body
        Returns:
        ByteArrayOutputStream containing bytes of body

      • unEscapeText

        public static java.lang.String unEscapeText(java.lang.String httpText)
        Makes '\n' and '\r' characters visible. Useful for debugging.
        Parameters:
        httpText - is the text you want to unEscape.
        Returns:
        string where '\n' and '\r' are visible
